# AGENTS.md — your onboarding

You are maintaining __CURVATURE_TITLE__, a Curvature app. This file is the
documentation; everything else is enforced, not remembered.

## The one command

```bash
./gate.sh        # ruff + pytest with coverage + curvature check
```

Green means done. Red means not done. `curvature check` findings are
called flat; each names the invariant it serves and the message
tells you the fix. If a finding seems wrong, stop and say so — never
route around the gate.

## Recipes

**Component**: `uv run curvature new component app/components/<name>` —
pours the file pair (component + test) already on-curve. Declare the
Props model first; the component is a pure function of it. Its CSS
lives beside it.

**Route**: reads render, writes redirect. No exceptions you can grant
yourself.

```python
@app.get("/things")
async def things(request: Request):
    return respond(request, thing_list(props), shell=shell)

@app.post("/things")
async def create_thing(name: Annotated[str, Form()]):
    store.add(name.strip())
    return redirect("/things")
```

Every fragment root carries an id. Forms are real forms, links are real
links — the constructors refuse anything else.

## The four nevers

1. Never write JavaScript. The boost layer is complete; behavior
   belongs on the server or in native HTML.
2. Never edit ratchet.toml. `uv run curvature ratchet` is the only hand on
   the mechanism.
3. Never bypass the gate — no skipped tests, no weakened assertions.
4. Never add a template language, bundler, client state store, or
   plugin registry.

## When you finish

Run ./gate.sh. If green and coverage rose, run `uv run curvature ratchet`
and include the tightened file in your change. Report what you built,
what the gate said, and every shortcut, doubt, or failed attempt that
shaped the result.
